1
00:00:00,150 --> 00:00:01,066
Ms. Carter,

2
00:00:01,066 --> 00:00:01,883
Congratulations,

3
00:00:01,883 --> 00:00:02,750
you're pregnant.

4
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:11,100
Wait, what?

5
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:12,750
Are you serious?

6
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:13,533
I...

7
00:00:13,850 --> 00:00:14,983
I'm 40!

8
00:00:15,316 --> 00:00:17,016
How could I be pregnant?

9
00:00:18,216 --> 00:00:18,833
Well, at 40,

10
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:20,016
it's considered a high-risk pregnancy.

11
00:00:20,216 --> 00:00:22,100
The baby's still in a fragile position,

12
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,616
so you need to be careful.

13
00:00:23,616 --> 00:00:25,500
No stress,

14
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,950
no physical impacts.

15
00:00:26,950 --> 00:00:27,616
otherwise,

16
00:00:27,616 --> 00:00:28,833
there's a chance of miscarriage.

17
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:30,183
Alright,

18
00:00:30,183 --> 00:00:31,983
I'll prescribe some medicine to help stabilize the pregnancy.

19
00:00:32,650 --> 00:00:33,450
No,

20
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:34,633
that's okay.

21
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:36,733
I don't need it, thanks.

22
00:00:48,216 --> 00:00:49,400
Mom,

23
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:50,283
I'll bring

24
00:00:50,283 --> 00:00:50,933
the test results home.

25
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,550
I'm sorry.

26
00:01:05,450 --> 00:01:06,016
You.

27
00:01:06,366 --> 00:01:07,700
It's you.

28
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:25,783
Mr. Zander,

29
00:01:25,783 --> 00:01:27,650
your mother's been urging you

30
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,366
to get married this year,

31
00:01:29,366 --> 00:01:30,766
and she wants a grandkid next year.

32
00:01:31,416 --> 00:01:32,133
Got it.

33
00:01:34,416 --> 00:01:35,216
Mr. Zander,

34
00:01:35,450 --> 00:01:36,883
the results haven't changed.

35
00:01:37,033 --> 00:01:38,633
Your chances of having a child...

36
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:39,433
well,

37
00:01:39,683 --> 00:01:41,016
are less than one in a million.

38
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:42,033
Mom,

39
00:01:43,566 --> 00:01:44,566
I've let you down.

40
00:01:46,066 --> 00:01:47,666
Your hope for a grandchild...

41
00:01:50,516 --> 00:01:52,016
is not gonna happen.

42
00:01:56,516 --> 00:01:58,016
I'm sorry.

43
00:02:25,983 --> 00:02:27,733
What's the point of all this money

44
00:02:27,733 --> 00:02:29,516
if I don't even have an heir?

45
00:02:29,516 --> 00:02:30,933
Alone...

46
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:33,900
that's what I'll be.

47
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:44,016
This guy's watch

48
00:02:44,350 --> 00:02:45,900
is high-end, custom-made.

49
00:02:46,316 --> 00:02:48,216
It's worth at least 20 million.

50
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:50,233
If I can snag him,

51
00:02:50,783 --> 00:02:52,000
I'm set for life.

52
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,883
That's for sure.

53
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:16,350
Here's your drink, sir.

54
00:03:29,633 --> 00:03:30,533
Sir,

55
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:32,716
you look like something's bothering you.

56
00:03:33,616 --> 00:03:34,833
How about

57
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:35,700
we share a drink?

58
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:37,250
Get lost.

59
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:39,250
Sir.

60
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:41,700
I'm not saying it again.

61
00:03:58,616 --> 00:04:00,200
Please, Mr. Clark,  I'm begging you!

62
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:01,950
Just give me a six-month salary advance.

63
00:04:02,416 --> 00:04:03,650
If I don't get the money,

64
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:04,700
my daughter

65
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:06,150
will be kicked out of school.

66
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:06,850
Please, help me.

67
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:07,833
No way!

68
00:04:08,166 --> 00:04:10,000
Look at your mess.

69
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,200
A mom with terminal cancer

70
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,550
and a kid in college.

71
00:04:13,816 --> 00:04:14,333
Plus,

72
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:16,750
you're always selling blood.

73
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:17,833
I don't even know

74
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:18,700
if you'll last another six months.

75
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:20,716
And if you don't?

76
00:04:20,716 --> 00:04:21,566
Who's gonna pay me back?

77
00:04:21,566 --> 00:04:22,533
Huh?

78
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:23,300
Me?

79
00:04:24,616 --> 00:04:25,700
It won't happen, I swear.

80
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,950
I'll work hard, please.

81
00:04:27,466 --> 00:04:29,766
Just this once,

82
00:04:31,150 --> 00:04:33,383
help me.

83
00:04:33,383 --> 00:04:34,500
Don't try to guilt me.

84
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,433
You want the job?

85
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:36,550
Do it.

86
00:04:36,816 --> 00:04:38,400
If not, get out!

87
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:41,916
Mr. Clark!

88
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,000
Mr. Clark!

89
00:04:43,816 --> 00:04:44,700
Mr. Clark!

90
00:04:44,966 --> 00:04:45,650
Mr. Clark!

91
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,100
Ugh, it's so hot...

92
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,550
Why is this drink hitting me so hard?

93
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:17,616
Sir, sorry,

94
00:05:17,916 --> 00:05:19,250
I'm just here to clean.

95
00:05:20,216 --> 00:05:21,166
Are you okay?

96
00:05:22,616 --> 00:05:23,300
Help me...

97
00:05:23,850 --> 00:05:25,166
I'll pay you.
